<section xmlns   ="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
         xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
         xml:id  ="rol-search"
         version ="5.0">
  <title>Searching Roles</title>
  <para>
    To start searching and managing Roles, you perform the following:
  </para>
  <orderedlist continuation="restart">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Log in to UID Administration.
      </para>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Click <emphasis role="strong">Role</emphasis> in the sidebar menu.
        <mediaobject>
          <alt>Sidebar Role</alt>
          <imageobject>
            <!--
             | The location of the image path must be relative to xml:base set
             | at the enclosing book element
             -->
           <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/images/en/rol/sidebar-lg.png" format="PNG"/>
         </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </para>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The Role page is displayed.
      </para>
      <figure xml:id="rol-search-home-fig">
        <title>Overview Roles</title>
        <mediaobject>
          <alt>Overview Roles</alt>
          <imageobject>
            <!--
             | The location of the image path must be relative to xml:base set
             | at the enclosing book element
             -->
           <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/images/en/rol/home.png" format="PNG"/>
         </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
  <para>
    To search for Roles, you can perform one of the following:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist mark='bullet'>
    <listitem>
      <link linkend='rol-search-basic'>Basic Search</link>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <link linkend='rol-search-advanced'>Advanced Search</link>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <link linkend='rol-operation'>Operations on Search Results</link>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <section xml:id="rol-search-basic">
    <title>Basic Search</title>
    <orderedlist continuation="restart">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          To perform basic search, enter a keyword in the global search criteria and click <emphasis role="strong">Search</emphasis> icon.
        </para>
        <figure xml:id="rol-search-basic-fig">
          <title>Basic Search Roles</title>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>Basic Search Roles</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <!--
               | The location of the image path must be relative to xml:base set
               | at the enclosing book element
              -->
             <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/images/en/rol/basic.png" format="PNG"/>
           </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          The results that match the global search criteria are displayed in a tabular format.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="rol-search-advanced">
    <title>Advanced Search</title>
    <orderedlist continuation="restart">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          To perform advanced search, click <emphasis role="strong">Filter</emphasis> icon to display the applicable search criteria.
        </para>
        <figure xml:id="rol-search-advanced-fig">
          <title>Advanced Search Roles</title>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>Advanced Search Roles</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <!--
               | The location of the image path must be relative to xml:base set
               | at the enclosing book element
               -->
             <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/images/en/rol/advanced.png" format="PNG"/>
           </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        <para>
          Enter the keywords in one or more of the following search criteria:
        </para>
        <itemizedlist mark='bullet'>
          <listitem>
            <para>Id</para>
            <para/>
          </listitem>
          <listitem>
            <para>Active</para>
            <para/>
          </listitem>
          <listitem>
            <para>Display Name</para>
            <para/>
          </listitem>
          <listitem>
            <para>Description</para>
          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          The results that match the entered search criteria are displayed in a tabular format.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="rol-operation">
    <title>Operations on Search Results</title>
    <para>
      This section describes the operations that you can perform based on selection of row(s) in the search results table.
      Only single selection operations are supported.
    </para>
    <para>
      You can perform the following operations by selecting a role from the search results table:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist mark='bullet'>
      <listitem>
        <link linkend='usr-create'>Creating a Role</link>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <link linkend='usr-modify'>Modifying Roles</link>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <link linkend='usr-delete'>Deleting a Role</link>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
</section>